 As the holiday season winds down, those of us who have the opportunity to travel relish the prospects of thinned crowds and good value. Sue Petrie, British Airways’ Commercial Manager for Southern Africa, says the airline has launched a worldwide sale, with savings of up to 20%. For example, World Traveller tickets from Joburg to London start at R9 862. Flights from Cape Town to London start at R10 815. Fares to Europe in Premium cabins have also been discounted by up to 20%. The sale applies to British Airways’ international and domestic flights. Seats are limited and available for sale until 29 January, with travel available in non-Premium until 23 December and Premium until 30 November 2018. Book at www.ba.com. 